<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/14028486-nadja-hertel"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1351433860i/14028486._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/14028486-nadja-hertel">Nadja Hertel</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Goon Squad is a fast read, and despite the non-linear timeline I didn&apos;t find it hard to follow the characters because each story is written in a way t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Goon Squad is a fast read, and despite the non-linear timeline I didn't find it hard to follow the characters because each story is written in a way that it can stand on its own. It's soooo much better when you read it the second time though, you pick up all the clever details Egan hid that you wouldn't see the first time around. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
