<div id="review_1358943190" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1358943190" />
    <a title="Steven Godin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26706841-steven-godin"><img alt="Steven Godin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621019440p2/26706841.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1358943190?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Steven Godin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Steven Godin" href="/user/show/26706841-steven-godin">Steven Godin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780307592835" href="/book/show/7331435-a-visit-from-the-goon-squad">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26706841-steven-godin?shelf=postmodern-fiction">postmodern-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26706841-steven-godin?shelf=america-canada">america-canada</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1358943190" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16986901825439769054">Not for me, had to push myself just to see it through to the end, and as for the PowerPoint section, what&apos;s the point?. I really do not understand all the praise, this book has put me off reading Pulitzer Prize winners for a very long time. Yes it was it was likeable in places, but with little character development and no flowing narrative, it felt like driving a car down a dead end side road. I can see why to others it might appeal, but apart from a few segments that were ok at best, for me any</span>
  <span id="freeText16986901825439769054" style="display:none">Not for me, had to push myself just to see it through to the end, and as for the PowerPoint section, what's the point?. I really do not understand all the praise, this book has put me off reading Pulitzer Prize winners for a very long time. Yes it was it was likeable in places, but with little character development and no flowing narrative, it felt like driving a car down a dead end side road. I can see why to others it might appeal, but apart from a few segments that were ok at best, for me anyway, it was such a drag to read, rather depressing, and just plain dull.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16986901825439769054" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
